body:
@EtK2000 firstly, you're wrong; my PR didn't add them to backends on purpose (so that everyone can agree on the exact `Input` changes before implementing them in backends), and yousiftouma actually did add them at least to LWJGL backend - and that's still better than nothing.

Secondly, you miss the main issue. Until you have the keys defined in `Input`, you can't use them in backends. It's completely mandatory to do the preliminary work in the `Input` class beforehand. The PRs weren't accepted for multitude of reasons (well, actually, mine got accepted, but got reverted due to a dumb typo), not implementing changes in backends weren't one of them.

I've been here for 4 years, and seen those issues from the very beginning. Believe me, I know what I'm talking about here.
